thread.title: Report: Eagles Interested In Brandin Cooks

author: CBS Philly
title: Report: Eagles Interested In Brandin Cooks
text:
— Chris Mortensen (@mortreport) March 2, 2017 
Chris Mortensen also reports that the Titans are the favorite to land Cooks, while the Eagles are second. Titans appear to be most likely suitor over Eagles, per one source, but nothing can be official until March 9, if it happens. @ESPNNFL 
— Chris Mortensen (@mortreport) March 2, 2017 
Cooks, 23, has over 1,000 receiving yards in each of the last two seasons. Cooks was the 20th overall pick in 2014. Brandin Cooks is 23. Has 75+ catches, 1100+ yards, 8+ TD's in both of his full seasons. Runs a 4.33! Not just a one trick pony, either.
